# Data Model

This document shows data model for the `mtsg` multi-tenant backend. It contains the main entities, their fields, and relationships.

---

## Notes

This model is intentionally simple and extendable. Future additions may include audit logs, plans/subscriptions, invitations, etc.

## Entities Overview

### Tenant

Represents an isolated customer or organization.

| Field       | Description                 |
| ----------- | --------------------------- |
| `ID`        | string (Unique PK)          |
| `Name`      | string                      |
| `CreatedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `UpdatedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `DeletedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `IsDeleted` | bool                        |


### User
A person who belongs to a single tenant and interacts with the system.

| Field       | Description                 |
| ----------- | --------------------------- |
| `ID`        | string (Unique PK)          |
| `TenantID`  | string                      |
| `Name`      | string                      |
| `Email`     | string                      |
| `CipherText`| string                      |
| `Role`      | string (admin or member)    |
| `CreatedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `UpdatedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `DeletedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `IsDeleted` | bool                        |

### Project
A resource owned by a tenant, created and managed by users.
| Field       | Description                 |
| ----------- | --------------------------- |
| `ID`        | string (Unique PK)          |
| `TenantID`  | string                      |
| `Name`      | string                      |
| `CreatedBy` | string (UserID)             |
| `CreatedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `UpdatedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `DeletedAt` | time.Time                   |
| `IsDeleted` | bool                        |

---

## Entity Relationship Diagram

```mermaid

erDiagram
    TENANT ||--o{ USER : has
    TENANT ||--o{ PROJECT : owns
    USER ||--o{ PROJECT : creates

    TENANT {
        string ID PK
        string Name
        time CreatedAt
    }

    USER {
        string ID PK
        string TenantID FK
        string Name
        string Email
        string CipherText
        string Role
        time CreatedAt
    }

    PROJECT {
        string ID PK
        string TenantID FK
        string Name
        string CreatedBy FK
        time CreatedAt
    }

```

---

## Multi-Tenancy Design Notes
- All entities include TenantID for scoping.
- No cross-tenant access is allowed.
- Auth token store the current TenantID and UserID.

---

## Indexing Strategy
- users - (tenantID, email) for login
- projects - (tenantID) 